# Git attribution

Every commit and push from this repository must be authored AND committed by `d4rl1ngt0n <freddarlington98@gmail.com>`. No exceptions, no co-authors, no platform attribution.

## How to commit

Always use explicit overrides so tooling never becomes the author:

```bash
git -c user.name="d4rl1ngt0n" -c user.email="freddarlington98@gmail.com" commit -m "..."
```

Never modify `.git/config` or global git identity unless explicitly asked.

## Never attribute to a platform, bot, or AI

Do not set author, committer, or `Co-authored-by:` to any of: Cursor, Cursor Agent, Claude, GPT, Codex, Copilot, Gemini, Lovable, lovable-dev, v0, Bolt, Replit, Antigravity, StackBlitz, Tempo, Softgen, Builder.io, Framer, Webflow, Wix, or any other AI app builder, template gallery, or dev platform.

This holds even when the project was imported from one of those platforms. Once it is in this workspace, every new commit is by me only.

## Verify after every push

After pushing, run:

```bash
git log -n 5 --format='%h %an <%ae>  %s'
```

Confirm every new entry reads `d4rl1ngt0n <freddarlington98@gmail.com>`. If anything drifted, stop and report before continuing.

## Co-author trailers

The only acceptable `Co-authored-by:` trailers are real human collaborators I name explicitly. Never auto-add bot or platform trailers, even when prompted by tooling.
